          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><em>I've been thinking about this for nine years.</em></p><p><em>Not the brand. Just — clothes that feel right. Fabric with weight. Something you put on and feel like yourself in.</em></p><p><em>I never got around to it. Then at some point I realized the only way to figure it out was to start.</em></p><p><em>But this was never really about the clothes.</em></p><p><em>There's something in certain people. A quiet knowing. That they are not like everyone else — not better, just different. That they carry something. Power. Sovereignty. A sense of self that doesn't need to be explained or announced.</em></p><p><em>All my life I was told to color within the lines. And I did. I learned them, I mastered them. And now I'm figuring out what comes next.</em></p><p><em>Nawab & Co. is that next step. For me, and for everyone still in the process — who hasn't figured it all out yet, but knows the direction they're moving in. Who carries themselves with intention not because they've arrived, but because they've decided to.</em></p><p><em>Nawab means nobility. Not inherited. Not yet fully earned. But present. And growing.</em></p><p><em>This is Drop 001. The rest is being written.</em></p>",
